      "parameters": {
        "width": 800,
        "height": 1040,
        "content": "# üü® Workflow Overview\n\nThis workflow automatically generates and refines personal bios using GPT-5. It takes input from a form or webhook, structures it, and produces a polished, professional bio ready to share on LinkedIn, websites, or portfolios.\n\n# üß© Sticky Notes Summary\n\n## üü© Trigger ‚Äî Webhook / Manual Input\n\nStarts the workflow when a user submits their details (like name, profession, and skills). You can connect it to any input source ‚Äî form, Notion, or Typeform.\n\n## üü© Data Clean-Up Node\n\nFormats and organizes raw input (e.g., removes extra spaces, corrects capitalization) before sending to GPT-5 for better results.\n\n## üü© GPT-5: Generate Bio Draft\n\nCreates the first version of the user‚Äôs bio using the structured input. The tone and style are adjusted based on the role and platform type (LinkedIn, portfolio, etc.).\n\n## üü© GPT-5: Polish & Improve Bio\n\nRefines the generated bio to make it sound more natural, polished, and professional. Adds structure and removes redundancy.\n\n## üü© Output Node ‚Äî Email / Notion / Google Docs\n\nSends the final version of the bio to your preferred destination. Ideal for quick publishing or saving for review.\n\n## üü© Optional: Log to Google Sheets\n\nStores generated bios with timestamps and input data for future reference or analytics.\n"
